author: Lori
comment: Comparison with the shipboard CTD cast was done for D0001. The shipboard CTD cast data are corrected for temperature, salinity, and depth (Redmine 14230). The L2 DO data product (corrected for temperature, salinity and depth) is lower for the glider compared to the shipboard data. This could be related to the issue of incorrect default salinity settings on some glider optodes (Redmine 13575).  Comparison to the shipboard bottle data is outside the scope of this project. Note: the conversion from ml/l to umol/kg for the shipboard DO = DO (ml/l) * 44.661 / 1.025.

author: Leila
comment:
recovered_host pressure record in the data file is a constant value of 93.8 dbar. 
The recovered_host CTD file in the DO folder are reporting one value: see (https://opendap.oceanobservatories.org/thredds/dodsC/ooi/lgarzio@marine.rutgers.edu/20181212T235659-CP03ISSM-MFD37-04-DOSTAD000-recovered_host-dosta_abcdjm_dcl_instrument_recovered/deployment0002_CP03ISSM-MFD37-03-CTDBPD000-recovered_host-ctdbp_cdef_dcl_instrument_recovered_20150509T010502.785000-20150509T010502.785000.nc.ascii?pressure[0:1:0])

This is in agreement with what the CTD file in the CTD folder are reporting: see (https://opendap.oceanobservatories.org/thredds/dodsC/ooi/lgarzio@marine.rutgers.edu/20181212T235133-CP03ISSM-MFD37-03-CTDBPD000-recovered_host-ctdbp_cdef_dcl_instrument_recovered/deployment0002_CP03ISSM-MFD37-03-CTDBPD000-recovered_host-ctdbp_cdef_dcl_instrument_recovered_20150509T010502.785000-20150509T010502.785000.nc.ascii?pressure[0:1:0])

Telemetered data are also missing.

There are data in the recovered_inst CTD folder see: (https://opendap.oceanobservatories.org/thredds/dodsC/ooi/lgarzio@marine.rutgers.edu/20181212T235146-CP03ISSM-MFD37-03-CTDBPD000-recovered_inst-ctdbp_cdef_instrument_recovered/deployment0002_CP03ISSM-MFD37-03-CTDBPD000-recovered_inst-ctdbp_cdef_instrument_recovered_20150509T010501-20151021T183501.nc.ascii?ctdbp_seawater_pressure[0:1:15839])

author: Lori
comment: Comparisons with the shipboard CTD casts were done for D0003 and D0006.The shipboard CTD cast data are corrected for temperature, salinity, and depth (Redmine 14230). The L2 DO data product (corrected for temperature, salinity and depth) from the glider is lower compared to the shipboard data (D0003 is substantially lower and could be related to the issue of incorrect default salinity settings on some glider optodes: Redmine 13575). For both comparisons, the difference between the downcast and upcast shows evidence of thermal lag. Comparison to the shipboard bottle data is outside the scope of this project. Note: the conversion from ml/l to umol/kg for the shipboard DO = DO (ml/l) * 44.661 / 1.025.

comment: Comparisons with the shipboard CTD casts were done for D0002, D0003 and R0001. R0001: glider chl-a values are higher at the surface, lower from 20-60 dbar and comparable at depth compared to the shipboard CTD. Further analysis using the shipboard bottle data should be conducted. This is outside the scope of this project.
